<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-191-112 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 567 919</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Sources  April 1991 v2 n4 p440(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Macweek 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Graph-in-the-Box Executive 1.14. (from New England Software Inc.)andO;(Software Review) (one of 12 presentation software packageevaluations in 'Graphics Snapshots')(Business graphics:presentations with clout) (evaluation)andM;</TITLE><SUMMARY>New England Software's $300 Graph-in-the-Box Executive 1.14 is apresentation graphics package that, because it is a terminate andstay resident (TSR) program, can import data from the screen whilethe user is working in another application.andP;  The program can popup at any time with a hot key combination, and offers mathematicaland statistical functions for the analysis and manipulation ofdata.andP;  The package offers a functional menu structure and userinterface, importing data files in ASCII and DIF formats, andexporting graphics files in CGM, EPS, HPGL, PCX and PIC formats.andO;The package includes 15 graph and chart types, and athree-dimensional effect is available in all but text charts.andO;Charts can be customized using nine fonts in unlimited sizes, ninefill patterns, 15 colors, and variable-width lines.andP;  Drawbacks toGraph-in-the-Box include an interface that is not the best andlack of mouse support.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   New England Software Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Graph-in-the-Box Executive 1.14 (Presentation software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationPresentation SoftwareBusiness Graphics.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Product information. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Graph-in-the-Box Executive 1.14andM;Graph-in-the-Box Executive 1.14 is a different breed of program, terrific atgrabbing data for a graph right from your screen while you're working inanother application.andP;  A text-based Terminate and Stay Resident (TSR) program,it pops up at your command and offers impressive mathematical and statisticalfunctions for manipulating and analyzing data.andM;The program's user interface and menu structure are functional, but lack thegood looks and intuitive design of the best programs.andP;  You use thebottom-line menus by moving the cursor or issuing the first letter of acommand; you can't use a mouse.andM;Data import formats include ASCII and DIF.andP;  The program exports graphicsfiles in CGM, EPS, HPGL, PCX, and PIC formats.andP;  In addition to capturing datafrom the screen, you can enter it from scratch.andM;Graph-in-the-Box Executive has 15 graph and chart types: vertical bar,horizontal bar, high-low, scatter, line, line/area, step, step/area, trend,spline, pie, linked pie, bar/line, text, and organizational charts.andP;  Athree-dimensional effect is available in all but text charts.andP;  You can set upbatches of graphics for printing, and use style sheets.andP;  There is a limitedslide-show capability using the batch feature to organize the slides inpresentation order.andM;You can customize charts with nine fonts in unlimited sizes, 15 colors, ninefill patterns, and variable width lines.andP;  Missing are a drawing feature andclip art.andP;  The program supports a variety of printers and plotters, but nofilm recorders.andM;If you use standard applications software to gather and work with data, usingGraph-in-the-Box Executive to grab the data and turn it into a chart for youmay not be worth it.andP;  Full-featured graphics programs often set up directlinks with spreadsheets, or at least have good importing capabilities.andO;However, if the idea of quickly and easily grabbing data from your screen toanalyze and display as a graphics image attracts you, be sure to take a closelook at this specialized software program.andO;</TEXT></DOC>